<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE AIR FARE CONTROVERSY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "Shopping for Emergency Air Fares" (by Lynn Simross, Jan. 26): 
</P>
<P>
I am writing to thank Simross on behalf of my sister and brother-in-law. Last 
Wednesday, my brother-in-law, Mike, was notified of the death of his father in 
Michigan. On Thursday morning Simross' article was in the View section. 
</P>
<P>
After trying two airlines with no success, he called American Airlines and the 
agent agreed to give them the discount air fare -- saving them approximately 
$1,000. 
</P>
<P>
To have to face this unexpected and unplanned-for expense when you are so upset 
just adds to your distress. So your information helped to ease the burden a 
little by saving them a considerable amount of money. 
</P>
<P>
SANDRA KLINE 
</P>
<P>
Lancaster 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
